# Escape — example standards (template)

These bullets are placeholders. Replace them with your real conventions.

## Game loop and time

- Use a **fixed simulation timestep** for movement and collisions; decouple rendering from `dt` when you add a render loop.
- Name the main update entry point consistently (e.g. `tick(dt)` or `update(fixedDt)`).

## Module layout

- Keep **one “system” per file** where it makes sense (e.g. `pickups.js`, `gameControls.js`).
- Prefer **plain functions + small structs** over deep class hierarchies unless you already committed to OOP.

## Style (JavaScript)

```javascript
// ❌ Avoid: magic numbers scattered in logic
if (x > 847) spawnBoss();

// ✅ Prefer: named constants near the system that owns them
const BOSS_SPAWN_X = 847;
if (x > BOSS_SPAWN_X) spawnBoss();
```

## What to tell the agent

- When you change behavior, say whether **save data / level format** must stay compatible.
- Call out **performance-sensitive** paths (collision, pathfinding, many entities).

